HELP CREATE KEY RANGE;
                                                           help                                                            
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                                     +
     CREATE KEY RANGE - This command is used to create a new key range. Since the key space is an ordered set,            +
                                                                                                                          +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                                   +
     CREATE KEY RANGE [ <keyRangeID> ]                                                                                    +
       FROM <lowerBound>                                                                                                  +
       ROUTE TO <shardID>                                                                                                 +
       FOR DISTRIBUTION <distributionID>                                                                                  +
                                                                                                                          +
     where lowerBound is a single value or comma-separated values for composite keys                                      +
     (e.g., "100, 'value'" for a two-column key)                                                                          +
                                                                                                                          +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                                              +
     This command is used to create a new key range. Since the key space is an ordered set,                               +
     it is enough to specify only one end of the range.                                                                   +
                                                                                                                          +
     For composite sharding keys, specify multiple values separated by commas that correspond                             +
     to each column in the distribution.                                                                                  +
                                                                                                                          +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                                               +
     <keyRangeID> - Unique identifier for the key range (optional, auto-generated if omitted)                             +
     <lowerBound> - Lower boundary value (inclusive). Can be integer, string, or comma-separated values for composite keys+
     <shardID> - Target shard ID where data in this range is stored                                                       +
     <distributionID> - Distribution ID this key range belongs to                                                         +
                                                                                                                          +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                                                 +
     Single column key range:                                                                                             +
         CREATE KEY RANGE krid1 FROM 1000 ROUTE TO shard1 FOR DISTRIBUTION ds1;                                           +
     Composite key range with two integers:                                                                               +
         CREATE KEY RANGE krid2 FROM 0, 100 ROUTE TO shard2 FOR DISTRIBUTION ds2;                                         +
     Composite key range with integer and varchar:                                                                        +
         CREATE KEY RANGE krid3 FROM 100, 'aaaaa' ROUTE TO shard3 FOR DISTRIBUTION ds3;                                   +
                                                                                                                          +
 TIPS                                                                                                                     +
     - Value bounds should be continuous and non-overlapping                                                              +
     - Use SHOW KEY RANGES to list existing ranges                                                                        +
     - Lock key ranges during maintenance operations with LOCK KEY RANGE                                                  +
     - Key ranges are immutable once created; use SPLIT or UNITE for modifications                                        +
     - Consider boundary values carefully to distribute data evenly                                                       +
                                                                                                                          +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                                         +
     SHOW KEY RANGES                                                                                                      +
     LOCK KEY RANGE                                                                                                       +
     UNLOCK KEY RANGE                                                                                                     +
     SPLIT KEY RANGE                                                                                                      +
     UNITE KEY RANGE                                                                                                      +
     DROP KEY RANGE
(1 row)

HELP DROP KEY RANGE;
                                              help                                              
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                          +
     DROP KEY RANGE - Removes a key range from the cluster. This deletes the key range metadata+
                                                                                               +
 SYNTAX                                                                                        +
     DROP KEY RANGE <keyRangeID>                                                               +
     DROP KEY RANGE ALL                                                                        +
                                                                                               +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                   +
     Removes a key range from the cluster. This deletes the key range metadata                 +
     but does not affect the actual data stored on the shard.                                  +
                                                                                               +
     Use DROP KEY RANGE ALL to remove all key ranges at once.                                  +
                                                                                               +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                    +
     <keyRangeID> - Identifier of the key range to drop                                        +
     <ALL> - Special keyword to drop all key ranges                                            +
                                                                                               +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                      +
     Drop a specific key range:                                                                +
         DROP KEY RANGE krid1;                                                                 +
     Drop all key ranges:                                                                      +
         DROP KEY RANGE ALL;                                                                   +
                                                                                               +
 TIPS                                                                                          +
     - Dropping a key range does not migrate or delete the underlying data                     +
     - Use SHOW KEY RANGES to verify which key ranges exist before dropping                    +
     - Consider the impact on routing before dropping key ranges in production                 +
                                                                                               +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                              +
     CREATE KEY RANGE                                                                          +
     SHOW KEY RANGES                                                                           +
     MOVE KEY RANGE
(1 row)

HELP LOCK KEY RANGE;
                                             help                                              
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                         +
     LOCK KEY RANGE - Locks a key range to prevent concurrent modifications. This is typically+
                                                                                              +
 SYNTAX                                                                                       +
     LOCK KEY RANGE <keyRangeID>                                                              +
                                                                                              +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                  +
     Locks a key range to prevent concurrent modifications. This is typically                 +
     used before performing operations like SPLIT or UNITE that require                       +
     exclusive access to the key range.                                                       +
                                                                                              +
     While a key range is locked, queries routed to it will wait until the                    +
     lock is released.                                                                        +
                                                                                              +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                   +
     <keyRangeID> - Identifier of the key range to lock                                       +
                                                                                              +
 TIPS                                                                                         +
     - Always pair LOCK with UNLOCK to avoid blocking queries indefinitely                    +
     - Use SHOW key_ranges to check the current lock status                                   +
                                                                                              +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                             +
     UNLOCK KEY RANGE                                                                         +
     SPLIT KEY RANGE                                                                          +
     UNITE KEY RANGE                                                                          +
     SHOW KEY RANGES
(1 row)

HELP UNLOCK KEY RANGE;
                                                  help                                                   
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                   +
     UNLOCK KEY RANGE - Releases the lock on a key range that was previously locked with LOCK KEY RANGE.+
                                                                                                        +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                 +
     UNLOCK KEY RANGE <keyRangeID>                                                                      +
                                                                                                        +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                            +
     Releases the lock on a key range that was previously locked with LOCK KEY RANGE.                   +
     After unlocking, queries routed to this key range will resume normal processing.                   +
                                                                                                        +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                             +
     <keyRangeID> - Identifier of the key range to unlock                                               +
                                                                                                        +
 TIPS                                                                                                   +
     - Always unlock key ranges after completing maintenance operations                                 +
     - Forgetting to unlock will block queries routed to the key range                                  +
                                                                                                        +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                       +
     LOCK KEY RANGE                                                                                     +
     SPLIT KEY RANGE                                                                                    +
     UNITE KEY RANGE                                                                                    +
     SHOW KEY RANGES
(1 row)

HELP SPLIT KEY RANGE;
                                                              help                                                              
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                                          +
     SPLIT KEY RANGE - Splits an existing key range into two key ranges at the specified boundary value.                       +
                                                                                                                               +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                                        +
     SPLIT KEY RANGE <newKeyRangeID> FROM <sourceKeyRangeID> BY <splitBound>                                                   +
                                                                                                                               +
     where splitBound is a single value or comma-separated values for composite keys                                           +
                                                                                                                               +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                                                   +
     Splits an existing key range into two key ranges at the specified boundary value.                                         +
     The new key range takes the upper portion of the original range (from the split                                           +
     point to the original upper bound), while the source range keeps the lower portion.                                       +
                                                                                                                               +
     Both resulting key ranges remain on the same shard. Use REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE                                            +
     afterwards to relocate one of them if needed.                                                                             +
                                                                                                                               +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                                                    +
     <newKeyRangeID> - Identifier for the newly created key range (upper portion)                                              +
     <sourceKeyRangeID> - Identifier of the existing key range to split                                                        +
     <splitBound> - Boundary value where the split occurs. Can be integer, string, or comma-separated values for composite keys+
                                                                                                                               +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                                                      +
     Split a key range at integer boundary:                                                                                    +
         SPLIT KEY RANGE krid2 FROM krid1 BY 100;                                                                              +
     Split a key range at UUID boundary:                                                                                       +
         SPLIT KEY RANGE krid4 FROM krid3 BY 'FF000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000';                                           +
                                                                                                                               +
 TIPS                                                                                                                          +
     - Lock the source key range before splitting to prevent concurrent modifications                                          +
     - The split bound must fall within the source key range boundaries                                                        +
     - After splitting, use MOVE KEY RANGE to relocate a range to another shard                                                +
     - Use UNITE KEY RANGE to reverse a split operation                                                                        +
                                                                                                                               +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                                              +
     LOCK KEY RANGE                                                                                                            +
     UNLOCK KEY RANGE                                                                                                          +
     UNITE KEY RANGE                                                                                                           +
     MOVE KEY RANGE                                                                                                            +
     CREATE KEY RANGE
(1 row)

HELP MOVE KEY RANGE;
                                                      help                                                       
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                           +
     MOVE KEY RANGE - Updates the routing metadata to assign a key range to a different shard.                  +
                                                                                                                +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                         +
     MOVE KEY RANGE <keyRangeID> TO <shardID>                                                                   +
                                                                                                                +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                                    +
     Updates the routing metadata to assign a key range to a different shard.                                   +
     This only changes where new queries for this key range are routed — it does NOT                            +
     migrate the actual data between shards.                                                                    +
                                                                                                                +
 WARNINGS                                                                                                       +
     - MOVE KEY RANGE only updates metadata. To move both metadata and data, use REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE instead.+
                                                                                                                +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                                     +
     <keyRangeID> - Identifier of the key range to move                                                         +
     <shardID> - Target shard ID to route this key range to                                                     +
                                                                                                                +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                                       +
     Move a key range to a different shard:                                                                     +
         MOVE KEY RANGE krid1 TO sh2;                                                                           +
                                                                                                                +
 TIPS                                                                                                           +
     - Use this command when data has already been migrated externally                                          +
     - For a complete migration including data, use REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE                                      +
     - Verify the target shard exists with SHOW SHARDS before moving                                            +
                                                                                                                +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                               +
     REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE                                                                                     +
     SHOW KEY RANGES                                                                                            +
     CREATE KEY RANGE                                                                                           +
     DROP KEY RANGE
(1 row)

HELP UNITE KEY RANGE;
                                                   help                                                   
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                    +
     UNITE KEY RANGE - Merges two adjacent key ranges into a single key range. The left key range absorbs+
                                                                                                         +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                  +
     UNITE KEY RANGE <leftKeyRangeID> WITH <rightKeyRangeID>                                             +
                                                                                                         +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                             +
     Merges two adjacent key ranges into a single key range. The left key range absorbs                  +
     the right key range, extending its upper bound to cover both ranges.                                +
                                                                                                         +
     The two key ranges must be adjacent (share a boundary) and must route to the same shard.            +
     After the operation, the right key range is removed.                                                +
                                                                                                         +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                              +
     <leftKeyRangeID> - Identifier of the left (lower) key range that will absorb the other              +
     <rightKeyRangeID> - Identifier of the right (upper) key range that will be merged into the left     +
                                                                                                         +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                                +
     Unite two adjacent key ranges:                                                                      +
         UNITE KEY RANGE krid1 WITH krid2;                                                               +
                                                                                                         +
 TIPS                                                                                                    +
     - Both key ranges must be adjacent and on the same shard                                            +
     - The right key range is removed after the operation                                                +
     - Lock both key ranges before uniting to prevent concurrent modifications                           +
     - This is the inverse operation of SPLIT KEY RANGE                                                  +
                                                                                                         +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                        +
     SPLIT KEY RANGE                                                                                     +
     LOCK KEY RANGE                                                                                      +
     UNLOCK KEY RANGE                                                                                    +
     SHOW KEY RANGES                                                                                     +
     DROP KEY RANGE
(1 row)

HELP REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE;
                                                   help                                                    
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                     +
     REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE - Moves a key range to a different shard, including the actual data migration.+
                                                                                                          +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                   +
     REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE <keyRangeID> TO <shardID>                                                     +
       [BATCH SIZE <batchSize>]                                                                           +
       [TASK GROUP <taskGroupID>]                                                                         +
       [CHECK | APPLY | NOWAIT]                                                                           +
                                                                                                          +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                              +
     Moves a key range to a different shard, including the actual data migration.                         +
                                                                                                          +
     The operation can be run in check-only mode to validate before applying, and                         +
     supports batch processing to control the migration pace.                                             +
                                                                                                          +
 WARNINGS                                                                                                 +
     - This command is not available for installations without SPQR coordinator.                          +
                                                                                                          +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                               +
     <keyRangeID> - Identifier of the key range to redistribute                                           +
     <shardID> - Target shard ID to migrate data to                                                       +
     <batchSize> - Number of rows to migrate per batch (optional, default 500)                            +
     <taskGroupID> - Task group identifier for tracking the operation (optional)                          +
     <CHECK> - Only validate the redistribution without applying changes                                  +
     <APPLY> - Validate and apply the redistribution (default behavior)                                   +
     <NOWAIT> - Start the redistribution and return immediately without waiting for completion            +
                                                                                                          +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                                 +
     Redistribute with default settings:                                                                  +
         REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE krid1 TO sh2;                                                             +
     Redistribute with custom batch size:                                                                 +
         REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE krid1 TO sh2 BATCH SIZE 100;                                              +
     Check redistribution without applying:                                                               +
         REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE krid1 TO sh2 CHECK;                                                       +
     Non-blocking redistribution:                                                                         +
         REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE krid1 TO sh2 BATCH SIZE 500 NOWAIT;                                       +
     Redistribute with task group for tracking:                                                           +
         REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE krid1 TO sh2 TASK GROUP taskgroup1;                                       +
                                                                                                          +
 TIPS                                                                                                     +
     - Use CHECK mode first to validate before applying in production                                     +
     - Adjust BATCH SIZE to balance migration speed vs. cluster load                                      +
     - Use NOWAIT for large migrations and monitor progress with SHOW task_group                          +
     - For metadata-only changes (when data is already on the target), use MOVE KEY RANGE instead         +
                                                                                                          +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                         +
     MOVE KEY RANGE                                                                                       +
     SHOW KEY RANGES                                                                                      +
     CREATE KEY RANGE                                                                                     +
     SPLIT KEY RANGE
(1 row)

HELP SHOW;
                                                 help                                                  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                 +
     SHOW - Displays cluster metadata, topology, configuration, and runtime status.                   +
                                                                                                      +
 SYNTAX                                                                                               +
     SHOW <target> [(<columns>)]                                                                      +
       [WHERE <condition>]                                                                            +
       [GROUP BY <column>]                                                                            +
       [ORDER BY <column> [ASC|DESC]]                                                                 +
                                                                                                      +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                          +
     Displays cluster metadata, topology, configuration, and runtime status.                          +
                                                                                                      +
     Valid targets: `databases`, `routers`, `shards`, `distributions`, `key_ranges`,                  +
     `key_ranges_extended`, `relations`, `reference_relations`, `pools`, `clients`,                   +
     `backend_connections`, `hosts`, `version`, `status`, `instance`, `sequences`,                    +
     `users`, `task_group`, `task_groups`, `task_group_ext`, `task_groups_ext`,                       +
     `move_task`, `move_tasks`, `redistribute_tasks`, `prepared_statements`,                          +
     `time_quantiles`, `unique_indexes`, `coordinator_address`, `is_read_only`,                       +
     `move_stats`, `errors`, `startup_finished`, `two_phase_tx`, `dcs_storage`,                       +
     `file_settings`, `tsa_cache`.                                                                    +
                                                                                                      +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                           +
     <target> - The metadata category to display (e.g., databases, shards, key_ranges, distributions) +
     <columns> - Optional column projection to display only specific fields (e.g., "(id, status)")    +
     <WHERE condition> - Optional filter to restrict rows by column values (e.g., WHERE id = 'shard1')+
     <GROUP BY column> - Optional grouping by a column                                                +
     <ORDER BY column> - Optional sorting by a column, with optional ASC or DESC direction            +
                                                                                                      +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                             +
     Show all shards:                                                                                 +
         SHOW shards;                                                                                 +
     Show key ranges with specific columns:                                                           +
         SHOW key_ranges (key_range_id, shard_id);                                                    +
     Show backend connections filtered by hostname:                                                   +
         SHOW backend_connections WHERE hostname = 'localhost';                                       +
     Show clients ordered by user:                                                                    +
         SHOW clients ORDER BY user DESC;                                                             +
     Show backend connections grouped by shard:                                                       +
         SHOW backend_connections GROUP BY shard_key_name;                                            +
                                                                                                      +
 TIPS                                                                                                 +
     - Use column projection to reduce output to only the fields you need                             +
     - Combine WHERE and ORDER BY for targeted diagnostics                                            +
     - Use key_ranges_extended for additional detail including shard names                            +
     - Use task_group_ext / task_groups_ext for extended task group information                       +
                                                                                                      +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                     +
     CREATE KEY RANGE                                                                                 +
     CREATE DISTRIBUTION                                                                              +
     REDISTRIBUTE KEY RANGE
(1 row)

HELP CREATE DISTRIBUTION;
                                                      help                                                      
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                          +
     CREATE DISTRIBUTION - Creates a sharding distribution with a distribution identifier and key column types.+
                                                                                                               +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                        +
     CREATE DISTRIBUTION <distributionID>                                                                      +
       [COLUMN TYPES <types> | (<types>)]                                                                      +
       [DEFAULT SHARD <shardID>]                                                                               +
                                                                                                               +
     where types is a comma-separated list of column types for the distribution key,                           +
     and each type is one of: INTEGER, INT, VARCHAR, UUID (VARCHAR/INTEGER may be followed by HASH)            +
                                                                                                               +
     where <shardID> is a default shard identifier. The <shardID> must exist.                                  +
                                                                                                               +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                                   +
     Creates a sharding distribution with a distribution identifier and key column types.                      +
                                                                                                               +
     A distribution defines the sharding key type layout used by attached relations and key ranges.            +
     Optionally, specify a default shard to route records that do not match any key range.                     +
                                                                                                               +
     For composite sharding keys (multiple columns), specify multiple types separated by commas.               +
     You can append "hash" after a column type to apply hash-based distribution to that column.                +
                                                                                                               +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                                    +
     <distributionID> - Unique identifier of the distribution                                                  +
     <types> - Distribution key column types in order (single or composite key)                                +
     <shardID> - Optional default shard identifier for unmatched routing cases                                 +
                                                                                                               +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                                      +
     Single integer key distribution:                                                                          +
         CREATE DISTRIBUTION ds1 COLUMN TYPES integer;                                                         +
     Single varchar key distribution with hash:                                                                +
         CREATE DISTRIBUTION ds2 COLUMN TYPES varchar hash;                                                    +
     Composite key distribution with two columns:                                                              +
         CREATE DISTRIBUTION ds3 COLUMN TYPES integer, integer;                                                +
     Composite key with mixed types and hash on second column:                                                 +
         CREATE DISTRIBUTION ds4 COLUMN TYPES integer, varchar hash;                                           +
     Parenthesized type syntax with default shard:                                                             +
         CREATE DISTRIBUTION ds5 (integer, varchar hash) DEFAULT SHARD sh1;                                    +
                                                                                                               +
 TIPS                                                                                                          +
     - Keep column type order aligned with relation distribution keys                                          +
     - Use hashed types for high-cardinality string/integer keys when needed                                   +
     - Configure DEFAULT SHARD only when fallback routing is explicitly required                               +
                                                                                                               +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                              +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION                                                                                        +
     DROP DISTRIBUTION                                                                                         +
     CREATE KEY RANGE                                                                                          +
     SHOW
(1 row)

HELP DROP DISTRIBUTION;
                                                 help                                                 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                +
     DROP DISTRIBUTION - Removes a distribution from cluster metadata, or all distributions at once. +
                                                                                                     +
 SYNTAX                                                                                              +
     DROP DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> [CASCADE]                                                    +
     DROP DISTRIBUTION ALL [CASCADE]                                                                 +
                                                                                                     +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                         +
     Removes a distribution from cluster metadata, or all distributions at once.                     +
                                                                                                     +
     Use CASCADE to remove dependent metadata objects (key ranges, attached relations) when required.+
     Use DROP DISTRIBUTION ALL to remove all distributions.                                          +
                                                                                                     +
 WARNINGS                                                                                            +
     - Dropping a distribution removes routing metadata and may impact attached relations.           +
                                                                                                     +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                          +
     <distributionID> - Identifier of the distribution to drop                                       +
     <CASCADE> - Also remove dependent metadata objects                                              +
     <ALL> - Special keyword to drop all distributions                                               +
                                                                                                     +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                            +
     Drop one distribution:                                                                          +
         DROP DISTRIBUTION ds1;                                                                      +
     Drop distribution with dependent metadata:                                                      +
         DROP DISTRIBUTION ds1 CASCADE;                                                              +
     Drop all distributions with cascade:                                                            +
         DROP DISTRIBUTION ALL CASCADE;                                                              +
                                                                                                     +
 TIPS                                                                                                +
     - Check current distributions and dependencies with SHOW before dropping                        +
     - Prefer dropping a single distribution instead of ALL in production                            +
                                                                                                     +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                    +
     CREATE DISTRIBUTION                                                                             +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION                                                                              +
     SHOW
(1 row)

HELP ALTER DISTRIBUTION;
                                                      help                                                      
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NAME                                                                                                          +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION - Modifies distribution metadata.                                                      +
                                                                                                               +
 SYNTAX                                                                                                        +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> ATTACH RELATION <relationName>                                        +
       DISTRIBUTION KEY <keys> [HASH FUNCTION <hashFunction>]                                                  +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> DETACH RELATION <relationName>                                        +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> ALTER RELATION <relationName>                                         +
       DISTRIBUTION KEY <keys> [HASH FUNCTION <hashFunction>]                                                  +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> ALTER RELATION <relationName>                                         +
       SCHEMA <schemaName>                                                                                     +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> ALTER RELATION <relationName>                                         +
       RENAME DISTRIBUTION COLUMN <oldColumnName> TO <newColumnName>                                           +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> ADD DEFAULT SHARD <shardID>                                           +
     ALTER DISTRIBUTION <distributionID> DROP DEFAULT SHARD                                                    +
                                                                                                               +
     where keys is a comma-separated list of column names (e.g., "col1, col2")                                 +
     where hashFunction is one of: IDENTITY, MURMUR, CITY                                                      +
                                                                                                               +
 DESCRIPTION                                                                                                   +
     Modifies distribution metadata.                                                                           +
                                                                                                               +
     Covers relation attachments, distribution key metadata, schema metadata,                                  +
     and default shard settings. This command operates on SPQR metadata and does                               +
     not execute table DDL on shards.                                                                          +
                                                                                                               +
     ATTACH RELATION attaches one or more relations to the distribution with a                                 +
     specified distribution key. For composite sharding keys, specify multiple                                 +
     column names separated by commas in the DISTRIBUTION KEY clause.                                          +
                                                                                                               +
     DETACH RELATION detaches a relation from the distribution.                                                +
                                                                                                               +
     ALTER RELATION DISTRIBUTION KEY replaces the entire distribution key of an                                +
     already attached relation. This overwrites all column names and hash functions                            +
     in one shot — it does not patch individual columns. Use this when you need to                             +
     change the key structure entirely, or to fix expression-based routing entries                             +
     (which RENAME DISTRIBUTION COLUMN does not support). The new key must have the                            +
     same number of entries as the distribution's column types.                                                +
                                                                                                               +
     ALTER RELATION SCHEMA changes the schema associated with an attached relation                             +
     in the distribution metadata.                                                                             +
                                                                                                               +
     RENAME DISTRIBUTION COLUMN is a metadata-only fix that renames a column in the                            +
     distribution key of an attached relation. It does not execute ALTER TABLE RENAME                          +
     COLUMN on PostgreSQL — it only updates the column name stored in SPQR metadata.                           +
     The primary use case is fixing a case mismatch between the column name in SPQR                            +
     metadata and the actual PostgreSQL column. For composite keys, call this command                          +
     once per column that needs renaming.                                                                      +
                                                                                                               +
     ADD DEFAULT SHARD sets a default shard for the distribution, routing records that                         +
     do not match any key range. DROP DEFAULT SHARD removes the default shard setting.                         +
                                                                                                               +
 WARNINGS                                                                                                      +
     - ALTER RELATION operations are metadata changes and may affect routing immediately.                      +
     - Use maintenance windows for key/schema metadata changes in write-heavy workloads.                       +
                                                                                                               +
 PARAMETERS                                                                                                    +
     <distributionID> - Identifier of the distribution to modify                                               +
     <relationName> - Relation to attach, detach, or alter                                                     +
     <keys> - Distribution key definition (column list and optional hash functions)                            +
     <hashFunction> - Hash function to apply to the key (IDENTITY, MURMUR, or CITY)                            +
     <schemaName> - Schema metadata value for an attached relation                                             +
     <oldColumnName> - Existing distribution key column name in metadata                                       +
     <newColumnName> - New distribution key column name in metadata                                            +
     <shardID> - Shard identifier to set as default shard                                                      +
                                                                                                               +
 EXAMPLES                                                                                                      +
     Attach relation with single distribution key:                                                             +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds1 ATTACH RELATION orders DISTRIBUTION KEY order_id;                              +
     Attach relation with composite key and hash function:                                                     +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds2 ATTACH RELATION users DISTRIBUTION KEY tenant_id, user_id HASH FUNCTION MURMUR;+
     Detach relation:                                                                                          +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds1 DETACH RELATION orders;                                                        +
     Replace relation distribution key:                                                                        +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds1 ALTER RELATION orders DISTRIBUTION KEY customer_id;                            +
     Change relation schema:                                                                                   +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds1 ALTER RELATION orders SCHEMA my_schema;                                        +
     Fix column name casing in metadata (w_id vs W_ID):                                                        +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds1 ALTER RELATION rc_test RENAME DISTRIBUTION COLUMN W_ID TO w_id;                +
     Set default shard:                                                                                        +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds1 ADD DEFAULT SHARD sh1;                                                         +
     Remove default shard:                                                                                     +
         ALTER DISTRIBUTION ds1 DROP DEFAULT SHARD;                                                            +
                                                                                                               +
 TIPS                                                                                                          +
     - Use CREATE DISTRIBUTION first, then attach relations and create key ranges                              +
     - Verify metadata after changes with SHOW relations and SHOW distributions                                +
     - Prefer replacing full distribution keys when relation uses expression-based routing                     +
     - For composite keys, call RENAME DISTRIBUTION COLUMN once per column that needs renaming                 +
                                                                                                               +
 RELATED COMMANDS                                                                                              +
     CREATE DISTRIBUTION                                                                                       +
     DROP DISTRIBUTION                                                                                         +
     CREATE KEY RANGE                                                                                          +
     SHOW
